.TH "snd_pcm_drain_done" 9 "snd_pcm_drain_done" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_drain_done \- stop the DMA only when the given stream is playback
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_drain_done
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
the PCM substream
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
After stopping, the state is changed to SETUP.
Unlike \fBsnd_pcm_stop\fP, this affects only the given stream.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if succesful, or a negative error code.
